parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash, and the Takata inflator recall has caused widespread concern and inconvenience for vehicle owners.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is on
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the airbag deploys unnecessarily
the seat belt sensor fails
and the vehicle is unable to be repaired due to parts unavailability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal has excessive play
the brakes fail to engage
and the vehicle accelerates out of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor resistor can cause the HVAC system to malfunction, leading to overheating, electrical fires, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The blower motor stops working
smells hot
or produces smoke; the resistor is melted or burned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without warning
causing the vehicle to lose control or resulting in injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can lead to inaccurate or missing information, causing confusion or accidents.
symptoms: The odometer hangs or does not update
the display is faulty
or the instrument cluster is unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repairs Not Completed or Effective
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to complete or effectively repair recalled components can lead to continued safety risks.
symptoms: The recall repair was not done or did not resolve the issue
and the component still fails or malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the remote entry system can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues.
symptoms: The remote entry system does not work
or the doors do not unlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate odometer readings can affect warranty and maintenance schedules, leading to potential safety issues.
symptoms: The odometer reading is inaccurate or inconsistent.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Rear Frame and Fuel Tank Mounting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the rear frame can cause the fuel tank to become unsecured, leading to a fuel leak and increased risk of fire in the presence of an ignition source.
symptoms: Loud noises from the rear of the vehicle
corrosion on the rear subframe
failure of the fuel tank to be repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect for Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delay in repair of recalled vehicles can lead to continued use of unsafe vehicles, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts not available for repair
excessive wait time for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of door locks and clips can prevent egress in an emergency, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Door locks not working
door releases not functioning
inability to exit vehicle quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air bag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Air bag lights illuminating continuously
failure of air bags to deploy
water seepage into instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks can cause corrosion, leading to structural damage and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water leaks into interior of vehicle
corrosion on exterior and interior components
mold and mildew growth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cosmetic issues can lead to decreased vehicle value and owner satisfaction.
symptoms: Scratches on truck bed
staining of interior seat fabric
water damage to carpet.
